     OOOOVVVVEEEERRRRVVVVIIIIEEEEWWWW
          ppppoooossssttttaaaalllliiiiaaaassss is a general purpose manager of private and public
          aliases (usually groups of names) that are used by post and
          sendmail programs (mailtool).  Post (4.0 and later) and
          mailtool can access these aliases either from the local
          machine or from a remote machine.  Postalias provides these
          capabilities:

          -  Create, submit, error-check, edit, and delete public and
             private aliases

          -  Convert aliases to email format (greatly speeds sending
             of mail)

          -  Provides "delete" (-name) syntax not provided by UPAS
             aliases

          -  List aliases and their respective locations

          -  Display alias members in user-selected format

          -  Search for alias names or text strings within alias files

          -  Send files (via uuto) to all members of an alias

