          PPPPoooossssttttaaaalllliiiiaaaassss understands the basic alias format and adds some
          additional capabilities.  The syntax of a postalias source
          file is shown below.  It is very similar to the UPAS alias
          format but in general is more "forgiving" about use of
          backslashes, blank lines, etc.  and has a few additional
          features.  Example alias files can be seen in the EEEEXXXXAAAAMMMMPPPPLLLLEEEESSSS
          section.  Alias names must contain a hhhhyyyypppphhhheeeennnn ((((----)))) and cannot
          contain: !!!! @@@@ %%%% ____ //// :::: ==== ....

          File aaaalllliiiiaaaassss----nnnnaaaammmmeeee:
            # Leading comments, if any

            alias-name                    # Optional - same as file name
            first.m.last/loc=POST_LOC     # Name/Loc avoids multiple matches
            f.m.last (optional comment)   # Optional Comment
            # Comment                     # Embedded Comment
            set LOCALQUAL loc=POST_LOC    # Optional Qualifier (saves typing)
